content:
The YouTube video was a recipe for vegan lasagna, and I was asking about possible substitutions for tofu in the ricotta layer. The creator responded with some great suggestions, and we ended up discussing different types of non-dairy cheese and their uses in vegan cooking. It was a really helpful conversation! 

And actually, I've thought about sharing my own recipes online, but I'm not sure where to start or if anyone would even be interested. Do you think it's worth considering?
